OL,6,FWhen challenged Ellis Wharton took up
OL,7,Fa "fighting stance", the court heard,
OL,8,Fas the officer attempted to restrain
OL,9,Fhim and the defendant responded by
OL,10,Flashing out and striking him in the
OL,11,Fchest.
OL,13,FAdam was arrested shortly afterwards
OL,14,Fwhen he was spotted by officers acting
OL,15,Fsuspiciously and later identified as
OL,16,Fbeing part of a group who entered the
OL,17,Flibrary.
