OL,6,FBoth pleaded guilty at an earlier
OL,7,Fhearing to burglary with intent to
OL,8,Fsteal while Ellis Wharton changed his
OL,9,Fplea on Thursday to admit assaulting
OL,10,Fan emergency worker.
OL,12,FEllis Wharton received an eight-month
OL,13,Fjail term for the burglary and a
OL,14,Fconsecutive three months sentence for
OL,15,Fthe assault.
OL,17,FJudge Flewitt says to Ellis Wharton:
OL,18,F"I accept but for the intervention of
OL,19,Fyour brother you would not have
OL,20,Fcommitted the offence of burglary.
