OL,6,F"Thankfully, the harm caused to PC
OL,7,FNielsen was modest. This was an
OL,8,Foffence against a person providing a
OL,9,Fservice to the public.
OL,11,F"I accept you played a subordinate
OL,12,Frole to your brother and that you
OL,13,Fimmediately expressed remorse for your
OL,14,Fdecision to join him in that
OL,15,Fenterprise."
OL,17,FThe judge told Adam Wharton: "You are
OL,18,Fthe older man, and I have no doubt you
OL,19,Finvolved and encouraged your younger
OL,20,Fbrother in the commission of this
OL,21,Foffence.
